_:N1858475a6c4f413faea163774cffe643 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Ben Gummer served as Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General from July 2016 until June 2017.</p>\n\n<p>He was elected Conservative MP for Ipswich in 2010.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"education\">Education</h2>\n\n<p>Ben was educated at Tonbridge School in Kent, and studied History at Peterhouse, Cambridge.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"political-career\">Political career</h2>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Parliamentary Advisor to Lord Feldman from May 2012 to September 2012</li>\n  <li>Parliamentary Private Secretary to Minister of State for International Development</li>\n  <li>Parliamentary Private Secretary to the Secretary of State for Education, October 2013 to May 2015</li>\n  <li>Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Quality at Department of Health from May 2015 to July 2016</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"career-outside-politics\">Career outside politics</h2>\n\n<p>After studying at Cambridge University, Ben ran a small engineering firm before becoming managing director of a consultancy business. He is also the author of a book on the Black Death - The Scourging Angel.</p>\n\n<p>Ben is an associate governor of Ravenswood Primary School, Patron of Home Start South Suffolk and a trustee of the Foundation Years Trust.</p>\n" .
